Scope of derivation
-------------------
This directory ships a single-file C++ extension that calls cuBLASLt
`cublasLtMatmul` on fp8 operands. The C++ source was authored for this repo;
no upstream TransformerEngine source files were copied or translated byte-for-byte.
The design was informed by reading TE's v2.13 implementation, specifically:

  transformer_engine/common/gemm/cublaslt_gemm.cu
  transformer_engine/pytorch/csrc/extensions/gemm.cpp

The cuBLASLt call sequence (descriptor creation, matrix-layout setup, fp8 scale-
pointer attributes, FAST_ACCUM, heuristic selection, workspace caching) follows
the public NVIDIA cuBLASLt API and the pattern documented there; those are API-
level facts, not copyrightable expression. The workspace cache keyed on shape
and a one-cublasLtHandle-per-process holder are independently implemented here.

Modifications relative to upstream
----------------------------------
Everything below is a from-scratch rewrite. There are no surviving upstream
lines. The "Modifications:" attribution that Apache 2.0 §4.b would require for
a derived work is not applicable because no file in this directory is a
derivative of a specific TE file; the closest upstream analog is acknowledged
here in NOTICE and in the README instead.

Later phases (backward kernel, deferred amax, Quantizer abstraction) may copy
small, load-bearing utilities from TE directly. Those files will carry the
original upstream copyright header alongside an explicit "Modifications:" line
per Apache 2.0 §4.b.
